{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}} {{Use British English|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Arthur Aaron | image = | fullname = Arthur Frederick Aaron | birth_date = October - December 1885 | birth_place = [[Liverpool]], England | death_date = | position = Forward | years1 = | clubs1= [[Southport F.C.|Southport Central]] | caps1= | goals1 = | years2 = 1907 | clubs2= [[Stockport County F.C.|Stockport County]] | caps2=2 | goals2 = 1 | years3 = 1906 | clubs3= [[St Helens Town A.F.C.|St Helens Recreation]] | caps3= | goals3 = | years4 = | clubs4= [[Accrington Stanley F.C. (1891)|Accrington Stanley]] | caps4= | goals4 = | years5 = | clubs5= [[Ashton Town A.F.C.|Ashton Town]] | caps5= | goals5 = }}
'''Arthur Frederick Aaron''' (born 1885) was a [[association football|footballer]] who played in the [[English Football League|Football League]] for [[Stockport County F.C.|Stockport County]]. He is the first player in alphabetical order in Football League history.<ref>*Joyce, Michael: "The Football League player's records 1888 to 1939 " ({{ISBN|1899468676}}).</ref>
