{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}} {{Use Australian English|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox AFL biography | name = Jack Doubleday | image = Jack Doubleday (before 1915).jpg | alt = | caption = | fullname = Jack Lindsay Doubleday | birth_date = {{birth date|1890|5|28|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Prahran, Victoria]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1918|10|30|1890|5|28|df=y}} | death_place = [[Indian Ocean]] | originalteam = [[Wesley College, Melbourne|Wesley College]] | height = <!-- ### cm --> | weight = <!-- ### kg --> | position = | statsend = 1915 | years1 = 1912–14 | club1 = {{AFL Uni}} | games_goals1 = 36 (17) | years2 = 1915 | club2 = {{AFL Mel}} | games_goals2 = 17 {{0}}(4) | games_goalstotal = 53 (21) | careerhighlights = }}
'''Jack Lindsay Doubleday''' (28 May 1890 – 30 October 1918) was an [[Australian rules football]]er who played with [[Melbourne University Football Club|University]] and [[Melbourne Football Club|Melbourne]] in the [[Australian Football League|Victorian Football League]].<ref>{{Ref AFL Encyc|10th|234}}</ref>
A dentist, Doubleday enrolled in the [[Australian Army Medical Corps]], but he died of [[influenza]] on his way to the [[Western Front (World War I)|Western Front]] in 1918, and was [[Burial at sea|buried at sea]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Roll of Honour – Jack Lindsay Doubleday|url=http://www.awm.gov.au/research/people/roll_of_honour/person.asp?p=573947|publisher=Australian War Memorial|accessdate=7 December 2010}}</ref>
