{{for|the novel by [[Dorothy L Sayers]]|Unnatural Death (novel)}} {{refimprove||date=September 2018}} '''Unnatural death''' is a category used by [[coroner]]s or [[medical examiner]]s and [[vital statistics (government records)|vital statistics]] specialists for classifying all human deaths not properly describable as [[death by natural causes]]. It includes events such as: * [[accident]]s * [[drug overdose]]s * [[execution]]s * [[murder]]s * [[Death by misadventure|deaths by misadventure]] * [[animal attack]]s * [[Complication (medicine)|complications]] of [[surgery]] * [[suicide]]s<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.slate.com/articles/news_and_politics/explainer/2009/12/what_exactly_are_natural_causes.html |publisher=Slate.com |title=What, Exactly, Are "Natural Causes"? |author=Palmer, Brian |date= 21 December 2009}}</ref> * acts of [[terrorism]] * [[war]]
